Tune in for two hours of music from women in the Americana genre today at 4pm. There’ll be some old favorites from artists such as Lucinda Williams, Bonnie Raitt, The Chicks, and Alison Krauss. And much, much more from performers making a name for themselves on the music scene or those that have been around […]

Did you know the US Post Office in Spanish Harlem is named after Tito Puente? It’s TP, Elio Reve, Omara Portuondo and the Puerto Rico All Stars on LATIN EXPLOSION. Friday, 7-9am, WSLR 96.5 FM Sarasota, stream at WSLR.org or listen anytime by typing WSLR LATIN EXPLOSION in your browser. “Oye Como Va!”

Our guest on the Peace & Justice Report this Wednesday, March 10 at 9am will be Bob Lord. Bob is a tax lawyer and former Congressional candidate, now an associate fellow at the Institute for Policy Studies. Bob’s work focuses on the relationship of tax law to inequality. He contributes to both the Inequality.org website […]

WSLR+Fogartyville T-Shirt Design Contest To celebrate our return of live music to the Fogartyville stage, WSLR+Fogartyville is holding a T-shirt design contest for FOGARTYVILLE. We are looking for a design that captures the purpose and vibe of our community space. WSLR+Fogartyville is accepting submissions for the 2021 Fogartyville T-Shirt Design Contest between March 1, […]
